Edgar Wrightington]].<ref name=SR>{{cite web|title=1904 Harvard Crimson Schedule and Results|publisher=Sports Reference LLC|work=SR/College Football|accessdate=February 27, 2017|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/harvard/1904-schedule.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gocrimson.com/sports/fball/history/Media_Center_Football_Yearly_Results |title=Harvard Football Yearly Records|work=GoCrimson.com |publisher=Harvard University |accessdate=August 13, 2014}}</ref>  [[Walter Camp]] selected only one Harvard player, halfback [[Daniel Hurley (American football)|Daniel Hurley]], as a first-team selection to his [[1904 College Football All-America Team]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Camp's Idea Of Football Stars: Yale Coach Puts Two Western Men in His Selection|work=The Daily Review (Decatur, IL)|date=1904-12-28}}</ref>\n\n==Schedule==\n\n{{CFB schedule\n|September 28| |{{cfb link|year=1904|team=Williams Ephs|title=Williams}}|[[Harvard Stadium]]|[[Boston|Boston, MA]]|W 24\u20130\n\n|October 5| |{{cfb link|year=1904|team=Bowdoin Polar Bears|title=Bowdoin}}|Harvard Stadium|Boston, MA|W 17\u20130\n\n|October 8| |{{cfb link|year=1904|team=Maine Black Bears|title=Maine}}|Harvard Stadium|Boston, MA|W 23\u20130\n\n|October 12| |{{cfb link|year=1904|team=Bates Bobcats|title=Bates}}|Harvard Stadium|Boston, MA|W 11\u20130\n\n|October 15|at|[[1904 Army Cadets football team|Army]]|[[The Plain (West Point)|The Plain]]|[[West Point, New York|West Point, NY]]|W 4\u20130\n\n|October 22| |[[1904 Carlisle Indians football team|Carlisle]]|Harvard Stadium|Boston, MA|W 12\u20130\n\n|October 29| |[[1904 Penn Quakers football team|Penn]] ([[Harvard\u2013Penn football rivalry|rivalry]])|Harvard Stadium|Boston, MA|L 0\u201311\n\n|November 5| |[[1904 Dartmouth football team|Dartmouth]] ([[Dartmouth\u2013Harvard football rivalry|rivalry]])|Harvard Stadium|Boston, MA|T 0\u20130\n\n|November 12| | Holy Cross|Harvard Stadium|Boston, MA|W 28\u20135\n\n|November 19|at|[[1904 Yale Bulldogs 