{"title_page": "Kyiv Boryspil Express", "text_new": "{{short description|Ukrainian railway airport rail link}}\n{{more citations needed|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox Rail companies\n|name           = Kyiv Boryspil Express\n|logo_filename  = Ukrzaliznytsya.svg\n|logo_size      = 100\n|image_filename = Kyiv Boryspil Express in Darnica.jpg\n|caption        = \n|franchise      = \n|nameforarea    = route\n|regions        = [[Kiev]] \u2013 [[Boryspil]]\n|secregions     = None\n|abbr           = \n|fleet          = 5 ''Pesa 620M''\n|stations       = \n|stationsop     = \n|parent_company = [[Ukrainian Railways]]\n|website        = {{url|https://kbp.aero/en/kiev-boryspol-express}}\n}}\n\n'''Kyiv Boryspil Express''' is an [[airport rail link]] between [[Boryspil International Airport]] and [[Kiev-Pasazhyrskyi]] opened in November 2018. The service is operated by [[Ukrzaliznytsia]], Ukrainian Railways.\n\n==History==\n[[File:620M-007 departs from Boryspil Airport.webm|thumb|Departure from Boryspil Airport Station]]\nInitially, the project was implemented by the State Agency for Investment and Management of National Projects of Ukraine. Financing was provided by [[Exim Bank of China|Eximbank of China]]. [[PricewaterhouseCoopers]] has developed a business plan for the implementation of the national Air Express project. In 2017, the project was stalled after a string of scandals.\n\nOn February 16, 2018, the [[Government of Ukraine|Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine]] allocated funds for the implementation of the project and the works commenced in May. According to Prime Minister [[Volodymyr Groysman|Volodymyr Groisman]], the overall cost of the railroad project is UAH 580 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kmu.gov.ua/ua/news/ekspres-do-borispolya-buduyetsya-z-viperedzhennyam-grafika-ekonomiya-koshtiv-po-robotah-sklala-vzhe-120-mln-grn-premyer-ministr|title=\u041a\u0430\u0431\u0456\u043d\u0435\u0442 \u041c\u0456\u043d\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 - \u0415\u043a\u0441\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441 \u0434\u043e \"\u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044f\" \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0454\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u0437 \u0432\u0438\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f\u043c \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0456\u043a\u0430, \u0435\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0456\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0448\u0442\u0456\u0432 \u043f\u043e \u0440\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0445 \u0441\u043a\u043b\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0432\u0436\u0435 120 \u043c\u043b\u043d \u0433\u0440\u043d, \u2013 \u041f\u0440\u0435\u043c\u2019\u0454\u0440-\u043c\u0456\u043d\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0440|last=Kitsoft|website=www.kmu.gov.ua|language=uk|access-date=2018-12-27}}</ref> The cost of the rolling stock isn't included in the project price tag though, only its refurbishment. The PESA build rail buses used had previously service in local rail traffic in rural parts of Ukraine. \n\nAt the end of November 2018, all necessary construction works were performed. Parts of the platform at track 14 at the Central Station in the capital Kyiv  was heightened to provide easy access to the trains and a new Boryspil Airport station was built some 200 meters north of the airport's Terminal D. Kyiv Boryspil Express officially launched on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unn.com.ua/uk/news/1765255-kyiv-boryspil-express-vidpravivsya-u-pershiy-reys|title=Kyiv Boryspil Express \u0432\u0456\u0434\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0432\u0441\u044f \u0443 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u0439\u0441|website=\u0406\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0435 \u0430\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0456 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 (\u0423\u041d\u041d). \u0412\u0441\u0456 \u043e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0456 - \u043d\u0430\u0439\u0441\u0432\u0456\u0436\u0456\u0448\u0456, \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0456, \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0456.|language=uk|access-date=2018-12-27}}</ref>\n\n==Service==\n[[File:Kyiv Boryspil Express at the station near Terminal D.jpg|250px|thumb|Kyiv Boryspil Express at the station near Terminal D]]\nThe service uses Class 620M units built by [[Pesa SA]]. \n\nTrains departure/arrive at the 14th track and run every hour (non-peak) and every 30 minutes (peak). Journey time one way is 30\u201340 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kyivpost.com/business/ukrzaliznytsia-launches-express-train-from-kyiv-to-boryspil-airport.html|title=Ukrzaliznytsia launches express train from Kyiv to Boryspil airport|date=2018-11-30|publisher=Kyiv Post|accessdate=2018-12-01}}</ref> Ticket price is [[Ukrainian hryvnia|UAH]] 80 and can be purchased by cash at two cash desks at the [[Kyiv-Passazhyrskyi|Central and South Railway Stations]], by noncash at four self-service terminals installed in the concourse over the 14th track and at [[Boryspil Airport railway station|Boryspil station]]. Passengers can also buy tickets on the trains using [[Contactless payment|contactless cards]].\n\n==Stations==\n{{Routemap\n|navbar = Kyiv Boryspil Express\n|title = Kyiv Boryspil Express\n|title-bg = #{{HeathExp colour}}\n|collapse = <includeonly>{{{collapse|no}}}</includeonly>\n|map =\nKBHFa~~  ~~{{stn|Kiev-Pasazhyrskiy}} {{rint|rail}} {{rint|kiev|1}}\nSTR\nSTR\nBHF~~  ~~{{stn|Darnytsia}} {{rint|rail}}\nSTR\nSTR\nKBHFe~~  ~~{{rint|air|link=Boryspil_International_Airport}} {{stn|Boryspil Airport}} \n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Station !! Image !! Time\n|-\n|{{stn|Kiev-Pasazhyrskiy}} || [[File:Fast trains at Kyiv Railway Station.jpg|150px]] || 0 mins\n|-\n|{{stn|Darnytsia}} || [[File:CAM02935.jpg|150px]] || 14 mins\n|-\n|Boryspil Terminal D|| [[File:\u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c.jpg|150px]] || 36 mins\n|}\n\n==Rolling stock==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#f9f9f9;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Class\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Type\n! colspan=\"2\" |Top speed\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Carriages\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Number\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Routes operated\n|- style=\"background:#f9f9f9;\"\n!&nbsp;mph&nbsp;\n!&nbsp;km/h&nbsp;\n|-\n|[[Pesa 620M]]\n|[[Railbus]]\n|75\n|120\n|1\n|5<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uz.gov.ua/press_center/up_to_date_topic/485818/|title=\u0428\u0432\u0438\u0434\u043a\u0456\u0441\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0435\u043a\u0441\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432-\u041f\u0430\u0441\u0430\u0436\u0438\u0440\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u2013 \u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u044c-\u0430\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0456 \u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u0443\u0454 \u0432 \u0448\u0442\u0430\u0442\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c\u0456 :: \u0410\u043a\u0442\u0443\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043c\u0430 :: \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0441-\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440 :: \u041e\u0444\u0456\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0432\u0435\u0431-\u0441\u0430\u0439\u0442 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0437\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0456|website=www.uz.gov.ua|access-date=2018-12-27}}</ref>\n|[[Kyiv]] \u2013 Boryspil\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Gatwick Express]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category-inline}}\n*{{Official website|1=http://swrailway.gov.ua/timetable/eltrain/?rid=239&lng=_en}} of the Ukrainian Railways\n*{{Official website}} with timetables\n* [http://kbp.kiev.ua/ Boryspil International Airport], official website {{in lang|uk|ru|en}}\n* {{NWS-current|UKBB}}\n\n{{Portalbar|Railways|Ukraine}}\n{{Ukrzaliznytsia}}\n{{Transport in Kiev}}\n[[Category:Airport rail links]]\n[[Category:Railway companies established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian Railways]]\n[[Category:Railway services introduced in 2018]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ukranian railway airport rail link}}\n{{more citations needed|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox Rail companies\n|name           = Kyiv Boryspil Express\n|logo_filename  = Ukrzaliznytsya.svg\n|logo_size      = 100\n|image_filename = Kyiv Boryspil Express in Darnica.jpg\n|caption        = \n|franchise      = \n|nameforarea    = route\n|regions        = [[Kiev]] \u2013 [[Boryspil]]\n|secregions     = None\n|abbr           = \n|fleet          = 5 ''Pesa 620M''\n|stations       = \n|stationsop     = \n|parent_company = [[Ukrainian Railways]]\n|website        = {{url|https://kbp.aero/en/kiev-boryspol-express}}\n}}\n\n'''Kyiv Boryspil Express''' is an [[airport rail link]] between [[Boryspil International Airport]] and [[Kiev-Pasazhyrskyi]] opened in November 2018. The service is operated by [[Ukrzaliznytsia]], Ukrainian Railways.\n\n==History==\n[[File:620M-007 departs from Boryspil Airport.webm|thumb|Departure from Boryspil Airport Station]]\nInitially, the project was implemented by the State Agency for Investment and Management of National Projects of Ukraine. Financing was provided by [[Exim Bank of China|Eximbank of China]]. [[PricewaterhouseCoopers]] has developed a business plan for the implementation of the national Air Express project. In 2017, the project was stalled after a string of scandals.\n\nOn February 16, 2018, the [[Government of Ukraine|Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine]] allocated funds for the implementation of the project and the works commenced in May. According to Prime Minister [[Volodymyr Groysman|Volodymyr Groisman]], the overall cost of the railroad project is UAH 580 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kmu.gov.ua/ua/news/ekspres-do-borispolya-buduyetsya-z-viperedzhennyam-grafika-ekonomiya-koshtiv-po-robotah-sklala-vzhe-120-mln-grn-premyer-ministr|title=\u041a\u0430\u0431\u0456\u043d\u0435\u0442 \u041c\u0456\u043d\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0456\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438 - \u0415\u043a\u0441\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441 \u0434\u043e \"\u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044f\" \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0454\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u0437 \u0432\u0438\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f\u043c \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0456\u043a\u0430, \u0435\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0456\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0448\u0442\u0456\u0432 \u043f\u043e \u0440\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0445 \u0441\u043a\u043b\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0432\u0436\u0435 120 \u043c\u043b\u043d \u0433\u0440\u043d, \u2013 \u041f\u0440\u0435\u043c\u2019\u0454\u0440-\u043c\u0456\u043d\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0440|last=Kitsoft|website=www.kmu.gov.ua|language=uk|access-date=2018-12-27}}</ref> The cost of the rolling stock isn't included in the project price tag though, only its refurbishment. The PESA build rail buses used had previously service in local rail traffic in rural parts of Ukraine. \n\nAt the end of November 2018, all necessary construction works were performed. Parts of the platform at track 14 at the Central Station in the capital Kyiv  was heightened to provide easy access to the trains and a new Boryspil Airport station was built some 200 meters north of the airport's Terminal D. Kyiv Boryspil Express officially launched on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unn.com.ua/uk/news/1765255-kyiv-boryspil-express-vidpravivsya-u-pershiy-reys|title=Kyiv Boryspil Express \u0432\u0456\u0434\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0432\u0441\u044f \u0443 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u0439\u0441|website=\u0406\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0435 \u0430\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0456 \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0456\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0456 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 (\u0423\u041d\u041d). \u0412\u0441\u0456 \u043e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u0439\u043d \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438 \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u044c\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0456 - \u043d\u0430\u0439\u0441\u0432\u0456\u0436\u0456\u0448\u0456, \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0456, \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0456.|language=uk|access-date=2018-12-27}}</ref>\n\n==Service==\n[[File:Kyiv Boryspil Express at the station near Terminal D.jpg|250px|thumb|Kyiv Boryspil Express at the station near Terminal D]]\nThe service uses Class 620M units built by [[Pesa SA]]. \n\nTrains departure/arrive at the 14th track and run every hour (non-peak) and every 30 minutes (peak). Journey time one way is 30\u201340 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kyivpost.com/business/ukrzaliznytsia-launches-express-train-from-kyiv-to-boryspil-airport.html|title=Ukrzaliznytsia launches express train from Kyiv to Boryspil airport|date=2018-11-30|publisher=Kyiv Post|accessdate=2018-12-01}}</ref> Ticket price is [[Ukrainian hryvnia|UAH]] 80 and can be purchased by cash at two cash desks at the [[Kyiv-Passazhyrskyi|Central and South Railway Stations]], by noncash at four self-service terminals installed in the concourse over the 14th track and at [[Boryspil Airport railway station|Boryspil station]]. Passengers can also buy tickets on the trains using [[Contactless payment|contactless cards]].\n\n==Stations==\n{{Routemap\n|navbar = Kyiv Boryspil Express\n|title = Kyiv Boryspil Express\n|title-bg = #{{HeathExp colour}}\n|collapse = <includeonly>{{{collapse|no}}}</includeonly>\n|map =\nKBHFa~~  ~~{{stn|Kiev-Pasazhyrskiy}} {{rint|rail}} {{rint|kiev|1}}\nSTR\nSTR\nBHF~~  ~~{{stn|Darnytsia}} {{rint|rail}}\nSTR\nSTR\nKBHFe~~  ~~{{rint|air|link=Boryspil_International_Airport}} {{stn|Boryspil Airport}} \n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Station !! Image !! Time\n|-\n|{{stn|Kiev-Pasazhyrskiy}} || [[File:Fast trains at Kyiv Railway Station.jpg|150px]] || 0 mins\n|-\n|{{stn|Darnytsia}} || [[File:CAM02935.jpg|150px]] || 14 mins\n|-\n|Boryspil Terminal D|| [[File:\u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c.jpg|150px]] || 36 mins\n|}\n\n==Rolling stock==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#f9f9f9;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Class\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Type\n! colspan=\"2\" |Top speed\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Carriages\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Number\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Routes operated\n|- style=\"background:#f9f9f9;\"\n!&nbsp;mph&nbsp;\n!&nbsp;km/h&nbsp;\n|-\n|[[Pesa 620M]]\n|[[Railbus]]\n|75\n|120\n|1\n|5<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uz.gov.ua/press_center/up_to_date_topic/485818/|title=\u0428\u0432\u0438\u0434\u043a\u0456\u0441\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0435\u043a\u0441\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441 \u041a\u0438\u0457\u0432-\u041f\u0430\u0441\u0430\u0436\u0438\u0440\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u2013 \u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043f\u0456\u043b\u044c-\u0430\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0456 \u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u0443\u0454 \u0432 \u0448\u0442\u0430\u0442\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0440\u0435\u0436\u0438\u043c\u0456 :: \u0410\u043a\u0442\u0443\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043c\u0430 :: \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0441-\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440 :: \u041e\u0444\u0456\u0446\u0456\u0439\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0432\u0435\u0431-\u0441\u0430\u0439\u0442 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0437\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0456|website=www.uz.gov.ua|access-date=2018-12-27}}</ref>\n|[[Kyiv]] \u2013 Boryspil\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Gatwick Express]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category-inline}}\n*{{Official website|1=http://swrailway.gov.ua/timetable/eltrain/?rid=239&lng=_en}} of the Ukrainian Railways\n*{{Official website}} with timetables\n* [http://kbp.kiev.ua/ Boryspil International Airport], official website {{in lang|uk|ru|en}}\n* {{NWS-current|UKBB}}\n\n{{Portalbar|Railways|Ukraine}}\n{{Ukrzaliznytsia}}\n{{Transport in Kiev}}\n[[Category:Airport rail links]]\n[[Category:Railway companies established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian Railways]]\n[[Category:Railway services introduced in 2018]]\n", "name_user": "Retimuko", "label": "safe", "comment": "ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyiv_Boryspil_Express"}
{"title_page": "Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma", "text_new": "{{For|avian infectious laryngotracheitis|Gallid alphaherpesvirus 1}}\n{{Infobox medical condition (new) \n| name            = Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma \n| synonyms        = immunoblastic lymphadenopathy (Lukes-Collins Classification), AILD-type (lymphogranulomatosis X) T-cell lymphoma (Kiel Classification)<ref name=who1>{{cite book |last=Swerdlow |first=S.H. |last2=Campo |first2=E. |last3=Harris |first3=N.L. |last4=Jaffe |first4=E.S. |last5=Pileri |first5=S.A. |last6=Stein |first6=H. |last7=Thiele |first7=J. |last8=Vardiman |first8=J.W |chapter=11 Mature T- and NK-cell neoplasms: Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma |title=WHO Classification of Tumours of Haematopoietic and Lymphoid Tissues |edition=4th |series=IARC WHO Classification of Tumours |volume=2 |publisher=IARC |year=2008 |isbn=978-9283224310 |chapter-url=http://apps.who.int/bookorders/anglais/detart1.jsp?codlan=1&codcol=70&codcch=4002&content=1}}</ref> \n| image           =  \n| caption         =  \n| pronounce       =  \n| field           = [[Hematology]] and [[oncology]] \n| \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma''' ('''AITL''', sometimes misspelled '''AILT''') (formerly known as \"'''angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy with dysproteinemia'''\"<ref name=Andrews>{{cite book |last=James |first=William D. |last2=Berger |first2=Timothy G. |title=Andrews' Diseases of the Skin: Clinical Dermatology |publisher=Saunders Elsevier |year=2006 |isbn=0-7216-2921-0 |display-authors=etal}}</ref>{{rp|747}}) is a mature [[T-cell]] [[lymphoma]] of blood or lymph vessel [[immunoblast]]s characterized by a polymorphous [[lymph node]] infiltrate showing a marked increase in [[follicular dendritic cells]] (FDCs) and [[high endothelial venules]] (HEVs) and systemic involvement.<ref name=who1/>\n\n==Signs and symptoms==\nPatients with this disease usually present at an advanced stage and show [[Systemic disease|systemic]] involvement. The [[Medical sign|clinical findings]] typically include a [[pruritus|pruritic]] [[skin rash]] and possibly [[edema]], [[ascites]], [[pleural effusion]]s, and [[arthritis]].<ref name=sie1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Siegert W, Nerl C, Agthe A |title=Angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy (AILD)-type T-cell lymphoma: prognostic impact of clinical observations and laboratory findings at presentation. The Kiel Lymphoma Study Group |journal=Ann. Oncol. |volume=6 |issue=7 |pages=659\u201364 |date = September 1995|pmid=8664186 |display-authors=etal|doi=10.1093/oxfordjournals.annonc.a059281 }}\n</ref><ref name=jaf1>{{cite journal |author =Jaffe ES |title=Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma: new insights, but the clinical challenge remains |journal=Ann. Oncol. |volume=6 |issue=7 |pages=631\u20132 |date = September 1995|pmid=8664181 |doi=10.1093/oxfordjournals.annonc.a059273 }}</ref>\n\n===Sites of involvement===\nDue to the systemic nature of this disease, neoplastic cells can be found in [[lymph nodes]], [[liver]], [[spleen]], [[skin]], and [[bone marrow]].\n\n==Causes==\nThis disease was originally thought to be a premalignant condition, termed angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy, and this atypical reactive lymphadenopathy carried a risk for transformation into a lymphoma. Currently, it is postulated that the originating cell for this disease is a mature (post-thymic) CD4+ [[T-cell]] that arises ''de novo'',<ref name=who1/> although some researchers argue that there is a premalignant subtype of this disease.<ref name=fri1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Frizzera G, Kaneko Y, Sakurai M |title=Angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy and related disorders: a retrospective look in search of definitions |journal=Leukemia |volume=3 |issue=1 |pages=1\u20135 |date = January 1989|pmid=2642571 }}</ref><ref name=smi1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Smith JL, Hodges E, Quin CT, McCarthy KP, Wright DH |title=Frequent T and B Cell Oligoclones in Histologically and Immunophenotypically Characterized Angioimmunoblastic Lymphadenopathy |journal=Am. J. Pathol. |volume=156 |issue=2 |pages=661\u20139 |date = February 2000|pmid=10666395 |pmc=1850038 |doi=10.1016/S0002-9440(10)64770-0 }}</ref> The [[Epstein\u2013Barr virus]] (EBV) is observed in the majority of cases,<ref name=who1/> being identified in the reactive (i.e. non-malignant) B-cells that comprise part of the polymorphous infiltrate of this disease.<ref name=wei1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Weiss LM, Jaffe ES, Liu XF, Chen YY, Shibata D, Medeiros LJ |title=Detection and localization of Epstein-Barr viral genomes in angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy and angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy-like lymphoma |journal=Blood |volume=79 |issue=7 |pages=1789\u201395 |date = April 1992|pmid=1373088 |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/79/7/1789.full}}</ref> These EBV+ B cells have numerous non-malignant crippling [[mutation]]s, often proliferate excessively, and in some cases may [[Malignant transformation|transform]] into EBV+ B cell lymphomas. The other cell types in these infiltrates, including the malignant T<sub>FH</sub> cells, are EBV negative. While the World Health Organization (2016) has classified these EBV-associated cases as one of the [[Epstein-Barr virus-associated lymphoproliferative diseases]] (see [[Epstein-Barr virus-associated lymphoproliferative diseases#Angioimmunoblastic T cell lymphoma|EBV+ angioimmunoblastic T cell lymphoma]], the role of the virus in the development and/or progression of EBV+ angioimmunoblastic T cell lymphoma is unclear.<ref name=\"pmid29885408\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Rezk SA, Zhao X, Weiss LM | title = Epstein-Barr virus (EBV)-associated lymphoid proliferations, a 2018 update | journal = Human Pathology | volume = 79 | issue = | pages = 18\u201341 | date = September 2018 | pmid = 29885408 | doi = 10.1016/j.humpath.2018.05.020 | url = }}</ref> Immunodeficiency is also seen with this disease, but it is a sequela to the condition and not a predisposing factor.<ref name=who1/>\n\n==Diagnosis==\n===Laboratory findings===\nThe classical laboratory finding is polyclonal [[hypergammaglobulinemia]], and other [[immunoglobulin]] derangements are also seen, including [[hemolytic anemia]] with [[cold agglutinins]], circulating [[immune complex]]es, anti-smooth muscle antibodies, and positive [[rheumatoid factor]].<ref name=who1/><ref name=sie1/>\n\n===Lymph node===\nThe normal architecture of a lymph node is partially effaced by a polymorphous infiltrate and residual follicles are commonly seen. The polymorphous infiltrate consists of lymphocytes of moderate size with pale/clear cytoplasm and smaller reactive [[lymphocytes]], [[eosinophils]], [[histiocytes]], [[plasma cells]], and [[follicular dendritic cells]]. In addition, blast-like [[B-cells]] are occasionally seen. A classic morphological finding is the aborization and proliferation of [[high endothelial venules]].<ref name=who1/> Hyperplastic [[germinal centers]] and [[Reed-Sternberg cells|Reed-Sternberg]]-like cells can also be seen.<ref name=quin1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Quintanilla-Martinez L, Fend F, Moguel LR |title=Peripheral T-cell lymphoma with Reed\u2013Sternberg-like cells of B-cell phenotype and genotype associated with Epstein\u2013Barr virus infection |journal=Am. J. Surg. Pathol. |volume=23 |issue=10 |pages=1233\u201340 |date = October 1999|pmid=10524524 |doi=10.1097/00000478-199910000-00008 |display-authors=etal}}\n</ref><ref name=ree1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Ree HJ, Kadin ME, Kikuchi M |title=Angioimmunoblastic lymphoma (AILD-type T-cell lymphoma) with hyperplastic germinal centers |journal=Am. J. Surg. Pathol. |volume=22 |issue=6 |pages=643\u201355 |date = June 1998|pmid=9630171 |doi=10.1097/00000478-199806000-00001 |display-authors=etal}}</ref>\n\n===Immunophenotype===\nAITL typically has the phenotype of a mixture of [[CD4]]+ and [[CD8]]+ [[T-cells]], with a CD4:CD8 ratio greater than unity. Polyclonal [[plasma cells]] and [[CD21]]+ [[follicular dendritic cells]] are also seen.<ref name=who1/>\n\n===Molecular findings===\nClonal [[T-cell receptor]] gene rearrangements are detected in 75% of cases,<ref name=fell1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Feller AC, Griesser H, Schilling CV |title=Clonal gene rearrangement patterns correlate with immunophenotype and clinical parameters in patients with angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy |journal=Am. J. Pathol. |volume=133 |issue=3 |pages=549\u201356 |date = December 1988|pmid=2849301 |pmc=1880823 |display-authors=etal}}\n</ref> and [[immunoglobin]] gene rearrangements are seen in 10% of cases, and these cases are believed to be due to expanded EBV-driven [[B-cell]] populations.<ref name=lip1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Lipford EH, Smith HR, Pittaluga S, Jaffe ES, Steinberg AD, Cossman J |title=Clonality of angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy and implications for its evolution to malignant lymphoma |journal=J. Clin. Invest. |volume=79 |issue=2 |pages=637\u201342 |date = February 1987|pmid=3805286 |pmc=424152 |doi=10.1172/JCI112860 }}\n</ref> Similarly, EBV-related sequences can be detected in most cases, usually in [[B-cells]] but occasionally in [[T-cells]].<ref name=wei1/><ref name=ana1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Anagnostopoulos I, Hummel M, Finn T |title=Heterogeneous Epstein-Barr virus infection patterns in peripheral T-cell lymphoma of angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy type |journal=Blood |volume=80 |issue=7 |pages=1804\u201312 |date = October 1992|pmid=1327284 |display-authors=etal |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/80/7/1804.full}}\n</ref> [[Trisomy]] 3, trisomy 5, and +X are the most frequent chromosomal abnormalities found in AITL cases.<ref name=kane1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Kaneko Y, Maseki N, Sakurai M |title=Characteristic karyotypic pattern in T-cell lymphoproliferative disorders with reactive \"angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy with dysproteinemia-type\" features |journal=Blood |volume=72 |issue=2 |pages=413\u201321 |date = August 1988|pmid=3261178 |display-authors=etal |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/72/2/413.full}}</ref><ref name=sch1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Schlegelberger B, Zhang Y, Weber-Matthiesen K, Grote W |title=Detection of aberrant clones in nearly all cases of angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy with dysproteinemia-type T-cell lymphoma by combined interphase and metaphase cytogenetics |journal=Blood |volume=84 |issue=8 |pages=2640\u20138 |date = October 1994|pmid=7919378 |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/84/8/2640.full}}</ref>\n\n==Treatment==\nThere is no proven or standard first-line chemotherapy that works for the majority of AITL patients.  There are several [[clinical trial]]s that offer treatment options that can fight the disease.  [[Stem cell transplant]]ation is the treatment of choice, with the allogeneic one being the preference because AITL tends to recur after autologous transplants.\n\n==Epidemiology==\nThe typical patient with angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma (AITL) is either middle-aged or elderly, and no gender preference for this disease has been observed.<ref name=who1/> AITL comprises 15\u201320% of [[peripheral T-cell lymphoma]]s and 1\u20132% of all non-Hodgkin lymphomas.<ref name=anon1>{{cite journal |title=A clinical evaluation of the International Lymphoma Study Group classification of non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. The Non-Hodgkin's Lymphoma Classification Project |journal=Blood |volume=89 |issue=11 |pages=3909\u201318 |date = June 1997|pmid=9166827 |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/89/11/3909.full |doi=10.1182/blood.V89.11.3909}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Rosai-Dorfman disease]]\n* [[Immunoblast]]\n* [[List of hematologic conditions]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n| DiseasesDB      = \n| ICD10           = {{ICD10|C|86|5|c|81}} ([[ILDS]] C84.460)\n| ICD9            = \n| ICDO            = {{ICDO|9705|3}}\n| OMIM            = \n| MedlinePlus     = \n| eMedicineSubj   = \n| eMedicineTopic  = \n| MeshID          = D007119\n| SNOMED CT       = 413537009\n| Orphanet        = 86886\n}}\n{{Hematological malignancy histology}}\n\n[[Category:Lymphoid-related cutaneous conditions]]\n[[Category:Lymphoma]]\n[[Category:Epstein\u2013Barr virus-associated diseases]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|avian infectious laryngotracheitis|Gallid alphaherpesvirus 1}}\n{{Infobox medical condition (new) \n| name            = Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma \n| synonyms        = immunoblastic lymphadenopathy (Lukes-Collins Classification), AILD-type (lymphogranulomatosis X) T-cell lymphoma (Kiel Classification)<ref name=who1>{{cite book |last=Swerdlow |first=S.H. |last2=Campo |first2=E. |last3=Harris |first3=N.L. |last4=Jaffe |first4=E.S. |last5=Pileri |first5=S.A. |last6=Stein |first6=H. |last7=Thiele |first7=J. |last8=Vardiman |first8=J.W |chapter=11 Mature T- and NK-cell neoplasms: Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma |title=WHO Classification of Tumours of Haematopoietic and Lymphoid Tissues |edition=4th |series=IARC WHO Classification of Tumours |volume=2 |publisher=IARC |year=2008 |isbn=978-9283224310 |chapter-url=http://apps.who.int/bookorders/anglais/detart1.jsp?codlan=1&codcol=70&codcch=4002&content=1}}</ref> \n| image           =  \n| caption         =  \n| pronounce       =  \n| field           = [[Hematology]] and [[oncology]] \n| \n| symptoms        = \n| complications   = \n| onset           = \n| duration        = \n| types           = \n| causes          = \n| risks           = \n| diagnosis       = \n| differential    = \n| prevention      = \n| treatment       = \n| medication      = \n| prognosis       = \n| frequency       = \n| deaths          = \n}}\n'''Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma''' ('''AITL''', sometimes misspelled '''AILT''') (formerly known as \"'''angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy with dysproteinemia'''\"<ref name=Andrews>{{cite book |last=James |first=William D. |last2=Berger |first2=Timothy G. |title=Andrews' Diseases of the Skin: Clinical Dermatology |publisher=Saunders Elsevier |year=2006 |isbn=0-7216-2921-0 |display-authors=etal}}</ref>{{rp|747}}) is a mature [[T-cell]] [[lymphoma]] of blood or lymph vessel [[immunoblast]]s characterized by a polymorphous [[lymph node]] infiltrate showing a marked increase in [[follicular dendritic cells]] (FDCs) and [[high endothelial venules]] (HEVs) and systemic involvement.<ref name=who1/>\n\n==Signs and symptoms==\nPatients with this disease usually present at an advanced stage and show [[Systemic disease|systemic]] involvement. The [[Medical sign|clinical findings]] typically include a [[pruritus|pruritic]] [[skin rash]] and possibly [[edema]], [[ascites]], [[pleural effusion]]s, and [[arthritis]].<ref name=sie1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Siegert W, Nerl C, Agthe A |title=Angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy (AILD)-type T-cell lymphoma: prognostic impact of clinical observations and laboratory findings at presentation. The Kiel Lymphoma Study Group |journal=Ann. Oncol. |volume=6 |issue=7 |pages=659\u201364 |date = September 1995|pmid=8664186 |display-authors=etal|doi=10.1093/oxfordjournals.annonc.a059281 }}\n</ref><ref name=jaf1>{{cite journal |author =Jaffe ES |title=Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma: new insights, but the clinical challenge remains |journal=Ann. Oncol. |volume=6 |issue=7 |pages=631\u20132 |date = September 1995|pmid=8664181 |doi=10.1093/oxfordjournals.annonc.a059273 }}</ref>\n\n===Sites of involvement===\nDue to the systemic nature of this disease, neoplastic cells can be found in [[lymph nodes]], [[liver]], [[spleen]], [[skin]], and [[bone marrow]].\n\n==Causes==\nThis disease was originally thought to be a premalignant condition, termed angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy, and this atypical reactive lymphadenopathy carried a risk for transformation into a lymphoma. Currently, it is postulated that the originating cell for this disease is a mature (post-thymic) CD4+ [[T-cell]] that arises ''de novo'',<ref name=who1/> although some researchers argue that there is a premalignant subtype of this disease.<ref name=fri1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Frizzera G, Kaneko Y, Sakurai M |title=Angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy and related disorders: a retrospective look in search of definitions |journal=Leukemia |volume=3 |issue=1 |pages=1\u20135 |date = January 1989|pmid=2642571 }}</ref><ref name=smi1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Smith JL, Hodges E, Quin CT, McCarthy KP, Wright DH |title=Frequent T and B Cell Oligoclones in Histologically and Immunophenotypically Characterized Angioimmunoblastic Lymphadenopathy |journal=Am. J. Pathol. |volume=156 |issue=2 |pages=661\u20139 |date = February 2000|pmid=10666395 |pmc=1850038 |doi=10.1016/S0002-9440(10)64770-0 }}</ref> The [[Epstein\u2013Barr virus]] (EBV) is observed in the majority of cases,<ref name=who1/> being identified in the reactive (i.e. non-malignant) B-cells that comprise part of the polymorphous infiltrate of this disease.<ref name=wei1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Weiss LM, Jaffe ES, Liu XF, Chen YY, Shibata D, Medeiros LJ |title=Detection and localization of Epstein-Barr viral genomes in angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy and angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy-like lymphoma |journal=Blood |volume=79 |issue=7 |pages=1789\u201395 |date = April 1992|pmid=1373088 |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/79/7/1789.full}}</ref> These EBV+ B cells have numerous non-malignant crippling [[mutation]]s, often proliferate excessively, and in some cases may [[Malignant transformation|transform]] into EBV+ B cell lymphomas. The other cell types in these infiltrates, including the malignant T<sub>FH</sub> cells, are EBV negative. While the World Health Organization (2016) has classified these EBV-associated cases as one of the [[Epstein-Barr virus-associated lymphoproliferative diseases]] (see [[Epstein-Barr virus-associated lymphoproliferative diseases#Angioimmunoblastic T cell lymphoma|EBV+ angioimmunoblastic T cell lymphoma]], the role of the virus in the development and/or progression of EBV+ angioimmunoblastic T cell lymphoma is unclear.<ref name=\"pmid29885408\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Rezk SA, Zhao X, Weiss LM | title = Epstein-Barr virus (EBV)-associated lymphoid proliferations, a 2018 update | journal = Human Pathology | volume = 79 | issue = | pages = 18\u201341 | date = September 2018 | pmid = 29885408 | doi = 10.1016/j.humpath.2018.05.020 | url = }}</ref> Immunodeficiency is also seen with this disease, but it is a sequela to the condition and not a predisposing factor.<ref name=who1/>\n\n==Diagnosis==\n===Laboratory findings===\nThe classical laboratory finding is polyclonal [[hypergammaglobulinemia]], and other [[immunoglobulin]] derangements are also seen, including [[hemolytic anemia]] with [[cold agglutinins]], circulating [[immune complex]]es, anti-smooth muscle antibodies, and positive [[rheumatoid factor]].<ref name=who1/><ref name=sie1/>\n\n===Lymph node===\nThe normal architecture of a lymph node is partially effaced by a polymorphous infiltrate and residual follicles are commonly seen. The polymorphous infiltrate consists of lymphocytes of moderate size with pale/clear cytoplasm and smaller reactive [[lymphocytes]], [[eosinophils]], [[histiocytes]], [[plasma cells]], and [[follicular dendritic cells]]. In addition, blast-like [[B-cells]] are occasionally seen. A classic morphological finding is the aborization and proliferation of [[high endothelial venules]].<ref name=who1/> Hyperplastic [[germinal centers]] and [[Reed-Sternberg cells|Reed-Sternberg]]-like cells can also be seen.<ref name=quin1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Quintanilla-Martinez L, Fend F, Moguel LR |title=Peripheral T-cell lymphoma with Reed\u2013Sternberg-like cells of B-cell phenotype and genotype associated with Epstein\u2013Barr virus infection |journal=Am. J. Surg. Pathol. |volume=23 |issue=10 |pages=1233\u201340 |date = October 1999|pmid=10524524 |doi=10.1097/00000478-199910000-00008 |display-authors=etal}}\n</ref><ref name=ree1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Ree HJ, Kadin ME, Kikuchi M |title=Angioimmunoblastic lymphoma (AILD-type T-cell lymphoma) with hyperplastic germinal centers |journal=Am. J. Surg. Pathol. |volume=22 |issue=6 |pages=643\u201355 |date = June 1998|pmid=9630171 |doi=10.1097/00000478-199806000-00001 |display-authors=etal}}</ref>\n\n===Immunophenotype===\nAITL typically has the phenotype of a mixture of [[CD4]]+ and [[CD8]]+ [[T-cells]], with a CD4:CD8 ratio greater than unity. Polyclonal [[plasma cells]] and [[CD21]]+ [[follicular dendritic cells]] are also seen.<ref name=who1/>\n\n===Molecular findings===\nClonal [[T-cell receptor]] gene rearrangements are detected in 75% of cases,<ref name=fell1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Feller AC, Griesser H, Schilling CV |title=Clonal gene rearrangement patterns correlate with immunophenotype and clinical parameters in patients with angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy |journal=Am. J. Pathol. |volume=133 |issue=3 |pages=549\u201356 |date = December 1988|pmid=2849301 |pmc=1880823 |display-authors=etal}}\n</ref> and [[immunoglobin]] gene rearrangements are seen in 10% of cases, and these cases are believed to be due to expanded EBV-driven [[B-cell]] populations.<ref name=lip1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Lipford EH, Smith HR, Pittaluga S, Jaffe ES, Steinberg AD, Cossman J |title=Clonality of angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy and implications for its evolution to malignant lymphoma |journal=J. Clin. Invest. |volume=79 |issue=2 |pages=637\u201342 |date = February 1987|pmid=3805286 |pmc=424152 |doi=10.1172/JCI112860 }}\n</ref> Similarly, EBV-related sequences can be detected in most cases, usually in [[B-cells]] but occasionally in [[T-cells]].<ref name=wei1/><ref name=ana1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Anagnostopoulos I, Hummel M, Finn T |title=Heterogeneous Epstein-Barr virus infection patterns in peripheral T-cell lymphoma of angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy type |journal=Blood |volume=80 |issue=7 |pages=1804\u201312 |date = October 1992|pmid=1327284 |display-authors=etal |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/80/7/1804.full}}\n</ref> [[Trisomy]] 3, trisomy 5, and +X are the most frequent chromosomal abnormalities found in AITL cases.<ref name=kane1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Kaneko Y, Maseki N, Sakurai M |title=Characteristic karyotypic pattern in T-cell lymphoproliferative disorders with reactive \"angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy with dysproteinemia-type\" features |journal=Blood |volume=72 |issue=2 |pages=413\u201321 |date = August 1988|pmid=3261178 |display-authors=etal |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/72/2/413.full}}</ref><ref name=sch1>{{cite journal |vauthors=Schlegelberger B, Zhang Y, Weber-Matthiesen K, Grote W |title=Detection of aberrant clones in nearly all cases of angioimmunoblastic lymphadenopathy with dysproteinemia-type T-cell lymphoma by combined interphase and metaphase cytogenetics |journal=Blood |volume=84 |issue=8 |pages=2640\u20138 |date = October 1994|pmid=7919378 |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/84/8/2640.full}}</ref>\n\n==Treatment==\nThere is no proven or standard first-line chemotherapy that works for the majority of AITL patients.  There are several [[clinical trial]]s that offer treatment options that can fight the disease.  [[Stem cell transplant]]ation is the treatment of choice, with the allogeneic one being the preference because AITL tends to recur after autologous transplants.\n\n==Epidemiology==\nThe typical patient with angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma (AITL) is either middle-aged or elderly, and no gender preference for this disease has been observed.<ref name=who1/> AITL comprises 15\u201320% of [[peripheral T-cell lymphoma]]s and 1\u20132% of all non-Hodgkin lymphomas.<ref name=anon1>{{cite journal |title=A clinical evaluation of the International Lymphoma Study Group classification of non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. The Non-Hodgkin's Lymphoma Classification Project |journal=Blood |volume=89 |issue=11 |pages=3909\u201318 |date = June 1997|pmid=9166827 |url=http://www.bloodjournal.org/content/89/11/3909.full |doi=10.1182/blood.V89.11.3909}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Rosai-Dorfman disease]]\n* [[Immunoblast]]\n* [[List of hematologic conditions]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n== External links ==\n{{Medical resources\n|  DiseasesDB     = \n|   ICD10          = {{ICD10|C|86|5|c|81}} ([[ILDS]] C84.460)  \n|   ICD9           = \n|   ICDO           = {{ICDO|9705|3}}\n|   OMIM           = \n|   MedlinePlus    = \n|   eMedicineSubj  = \n|   eMedicineTopic = \n|   MeshID         = D007119 \n}}\n{{Hematological malignancy histology}}\n\n[[Category:Lymphoid-related cutaneous conditions]]\n[[Category:Lymphoma]]\n[[Category:Epstein\u2013Barr virus-associated diseases]]\n", "name_user": "Dismanet", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding new medical resources.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angioimmunoblastic_T-cell_lymphoma"}
{"title_page": "S\u00e9bastien Rosseler", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2010}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = S\u00e9bastien Rosseler\n| image         = S\u00e9bastien Rosseler - Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9 2012 - Prologue.jpg\n| caption       = Rosseler at the [[2012 Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9]]\n| fullname      = S\u00e9bastien Rosseler\n| nickname      = S\u00e9ba\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1981|7|15}}\n| birth_place   = [[Verviers]], [[Wallonia]], Belgium\n| height        = {{height|m=1.82|precision=0}}\n| weight        = {{convert|77|kg|lb|abbr=on}}\n| currentteam   = Veranclassic-Doltcini\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     = Classics specialist\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     = 2002\n| proteam1      = '''[[Stagiaire (cycling)|\u2192]]''' {{ct|DFF|2002}}\n| proyears2     = 2003\n| proteam2      = {{ct|QST|2003}}\n| proyears3     = 2004\n| proteam3      = {{ct|REG|2004}}\n| proyears4     = 2005\u20132009\n| proteam4      = {{ct|QST|2005}}\n| proyears5     = 2010\u20132011\n| proteam5      = {{ct|RSH|2010}}\n| proyears6     = 2012\u20132013\n| proteam6      = {{ct|GRM|2012a}}\n| proyears7     = 2014\u2013\n| proteam7      = Veranclassic-Doltcini\n| majorwins     = '''[[Grand Tour (cycling)|Grand Tours]]'''\n:'''[[Giro d'Italia]]'''\n::1 TTT stage ([[2012 Giro d'Italia|2012]])\n'''[[Race stage|Stage races]]'''\n:[[Three Days of De Panne]] ([[2011 Three Days of De Panne|2011]])\n'''[[Classic cycle races|One-day races and Classics]]'''\n:[[Brabantse Pijl]] ([[2010 Brabantse Pijl|2010]])\n}}\n'''S\u00e9bastien Rosseler''' (born 15 July 1981) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] professional [[road racing cyclist]] who rides for Veranclassic-Doltcini.<ref name=\"2014team\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://62.50.72.82/ucinet/default.asp?page=UCITeamsdetail&discipline=ROA&continent=EUR&teamscategory=CTM&teamstype=CTM&year=2013&teamnameid=3846&npage=&search=&l=FRA|title=Veranclassic\u2013Doltcini (DOL)&nbsp;\u2013 BEL|accessdate=21 January 2014|work=[[UCI Continental Circuits]]|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|location=[[Aigle]], [[Vaud]]}}</ref> Between 2012 and 2013, Rosseler competed with [[UCI ProTeam]] {{ct|GRS|2012a}}.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/no-contract-for-rosseler-at-garmin-sharp|title=No contract for Rosseler at Garmin-Sharp|work=[[Cyclingnews.com]]|publisher=[[Future plc]]|location=[[Bath, Somerset|Bath]], [[England]]|date=5 October 2013|accessdate=5 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/cnt/dmf20131004_00776062|language=Dutch|title=Rosseler moet weg bij Garmin-Sharp|trans-title=Rosseler leaves Garmin-Sharp|work=[[Het Nieuwsblad]]|publisher=[[Corelio]]|location=[[Antwerp]], [[Flanders]]|date=5 October 2013|accessdate=24 October 2013}}</ref> Born in [[Verviers]], [[Wallonia]], Belgium, Rosseler currently resides in [[Tongeren]], [[Flanders]], Belgium.<ref name=\"2014team\">{{cite news|url=http://veranclassic-doltcini.be/rosseler.html|title=S\u00e9bastien Rosseler at Veranclassic\u2013Doltcini|date=21 January 2014|access-date=6 January 2014|work=Veranclassic\u2013Doltcini|publisher=Geoffrey Coup\u00e9|location=[[Jemappes]], [[Walloon Region|Walloon]]|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222143703/http://veranclassic-doltcini.be/rosseler.html|archive-date=22 February 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Career achievements==\n===Major results===\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n;2002\n: 1st [[File:Jersey yellow.svg|20px]] Overall [[Le Triptyque des Monts et Ch\u00e2teaux]]\n;2003\n: 1st [[File:Jersey yellow.svg|20px]] Overall [[Le Triptyque des Monts et Ch\u00e2teaux]]\n: [[Olympia's Tour]]\n::1st [[File:Jersey green.svg|20px|Green jersey]] Points classification\n::1st Stages 1, 6 & 7 ([[Individual time trial|ITT]])\n: 6th [[De Vlaamse Pijl]]\n;2004\n: 8th Overall [[Four Days of Dunkirk]]\n: 9th [[2006 Gent\u201